TITLE: Running Jellyfin Server from Command Line
DESCRIPTION: This command demonstrates how to run the Jellyfin server directly from the source code using the dotnet CLI, specifying the web client directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
cd jellyfin                          # Move into the repository directory
dotnet run --project Jellyfin.Server --webdir /absolute/path/to/jellyfin-web/dist # Run the server startup project
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Building Jellyfin from Source
DESCRIPTION: These commands build the Jellyfin project and navigate to the output directory to prepare for running the executable directly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
dotnet build                       # Build the project
cd Jellyfin.Server/bin/Debug/net9.0 # Change into the build output directory
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Running Jellyfin Tests via Command Line
DESCRIPTION: Command to execute Jellyfin unit tests from the command line interface using the dotnet CLI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
dotnet test
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Cloning the Jellyfin Repository via HTTPS
DESCRIPTION: This command clones the Jellyfin repository from GitHub to your local machine using HTTPS protocol.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
git clone https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin.git
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing AFL++ Fuzzing Framework
DESCRIPTION: Commands to clone and install the AFL++ fuzzing framework from GitHub. Requires make and sudo privileges.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/fuzz/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
git clone https://github.com/AFLplusplus/AFLplusplus
cd AFLplusplus
make all
sudo make install
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing SharpFuzz CommandLine Tool
DESCRIPTION: Command to install the SharpFuzz.CommandLine tool globally using the .NET CLI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/fuzz/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
dotnet tool install --global SharpFuzz.CommandLine
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: EFCore Migrations Command Syntax
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the general syntax for creating EFCore migrations with a specific provider. It demonstrates how to specify the project path and provider key.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/src/Jellyfin.Database/readme.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cmd
CODE:
```
dotnet ef migrations add MIGRATION_NAME --project "PATH_TO_PROJECT" -- --provider PROVIDER_KEY
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating SQLite Migrations in Jellyfin
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create SQLite migrations for Jellyfin. It specifies the SQLite provider project path and the Jellyfin-SQLite migration provider key.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/src/Jellyfin.Database/readme.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: cmd
CODE:
```
dotnet ef migrations add {MIGRATION_NAME} --project "src/Jellyfin.Database/Jellyfin.Database.Providers.Sqlite" -- --migration-provider Jellyfin-SQLite
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Setting Jellyfin No Web Client Environment Variable
DESCRIPTION: Environment variable setting to disable web client hosting in Jellyfin server.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
JELLYFIN_NOWEBCONTENT=true
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Jellyfin No Web Client Command Line Flag
DESCRIPTION: Command line switch to disable web client hosting in Jellyfin server.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
--nowebclient
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding Jellyfin Docker Template Repository URL
DESCRIPTION: The URL to add to unRAID's template repositories for accessing Jellyfin Docker templates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/deployment/unraid/docker-templates/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/tree/master/deployment/unraid/docker-templates
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Accessing Task<T> Result Property in C#
DESCRIPTION: This signature represents the Result property of a generic Task<T> class, which returns the result of the asynchronous operation when it completes successfully.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/BannedSymbols.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
P:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1.Result
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Comparing Guid Equality Using Equality Operator in C#
DESCRIPTION: This method signature represents the equality operator (==) for comparing two System.Guid objects. It returns a boolean indicating whether the two Guids are equal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/BannedSymbols.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
M:System.Guid.op_Equality(System.Guid,System.Guid)
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Comparing Guid Inequality Using Inequality Operator in C#
DESCRIPTION: This method signature represents the inequality operator (!=) for comparing two System.Guid objects. It returns a boolean indicating whether the two Guids are not equal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/BannedSymbols.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
M:System.Guid.op_Inequality(System.Guid,System.Guid)
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Comparing Guid Equality Using Equals Method in C#
DESCRIPTION: This method signature represents the Equals method of the System.Guid class, which compares the current Guid with another object. It returns a boolean indicating whether the objects are equal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/BannedSymbols.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
M:System.Guid.Equals(System.Object)
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Markdown Contributors List
DESCRIPTION: A markdown formatted list of GitHub usernames with profile links for Jellyfin project contributors
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTORS.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
# Jellyfin Contributors\n\n - [1337joe](https://github.com/1337joe)\n - [97carmine](https://github.com/97carmine)\n[...]
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: URL Query Parameter String in Percent-Encoded Format
DESCRIPTION: A URL-encoded query string containing three key-value pairs: a=1, b=2, and c=3. The string uses percent encoding where %3D represents '=' and %26 represents '&', which are used to separate keys from values and key-value pairs from each other respectively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/fuzz/Jellyfin.Api.Fuzz/Testcases/UrlDecodeQueryFeature/test1.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
a%3D1%26b%3D2%26c%3D3
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Jellyfin Media Thumbnail Path with Metadata
DESCRIPTION: A file path for a Family Guy episode thumbnail with associated metadata including timestamp, image type designation, resolution dimensions (1920x1080), and an identifier hash. This format is used by Jellyfin to track media assets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin/blob/master/fuzz/Emby.Server.Implementations.Fuzz/Testcases/SqliteItemRepository.ItemImageInfoFromValueString/test1.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
/mnt/series/Family Guy/Season 1/Family Guy - S01E01-thumb.jpg*637452096478512963*Primary*1920*1080*WjQbtJtSO8nhNZ%L_Io#R/oaS6o}-;adXAoIn7j[%hW9s:WGw[nN
```

LANGUAGE: CSV
CODE:

```
packet,0.375000,__
packet,0.167000,__
packet,0.042000,__
packet,0.083000,__
// ... (truncated for brevity)
packet,21.438000,__
```
